<p>In IE7, If you call <code>fadeIn/Out</code> on inline element, jQuery will add <code>zoom: 1</code> to the element which virtually makes the element <code>inline-block</code>. This will cause an undesired effect -- a line-break is inserted in front of the <code>inline-block</code> element.</p>  <p>I can disable <code>zoom: 1</code> by adding <code>*zoom: 0 !important</code>. But this removes the <code>fadeIn/Out</code> transition effect.</p>  <p>I want to keep the <code>fadeIn/Out</code> transition effect and remove the line-break. How can I make it??</p>  <pre><code>&lt;html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"&gt; &lt;head&gt;     &lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;     &lt;meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=7" /&gt;     &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.1.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;     &lt;script&gt;         $(function () {             $('.fade').click(function () {                 $(this).fadeOut(800).delay(800).fadeIn(800);             });         });     &lt;/script&gt;     &lt;style&gt;         /* .fade {             *zoom: 0 !important;         } */ /* ^ This rule removes the `block`style of inline element */              .fade:hover {                 background-color: #cde5fe;             }     &lt;/style&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt;     &lt;span&gt;text text text text text text text text text text text text text. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="fade"&gt;please please please please please click this sentence. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;text text text text text text text text text text text text text. &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>